The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	St Johns: Chris Gayle will be rested for the West Indies sole Twenty20 International against Zimbabwe this Sunday at Queens Park Oval in Trinidad, the West Indies Cricket Board (WICB) announced. The West Indies captain was not included in a 13-member squad for the match, but a WICB media release Tuesday indicated that he is expected to be available for the five ODIs against the Zimbabweans. In Gayles absence, wicket-keeper Denesh Ramdin, the deputy in the just-concluded limited-overs series against Australia, will lead the side.        
	Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board chairman Ijaz Butt Wednesday said the new coach for the national team would be a Pakistani and not a foreigner. He said the PCB agreed not to have a foreign coach after high-profile candidates, Greg Chappell and Mickey Arthur showed no interest.        
	Dubai: The Indo-Belarussian pair of Mahesh Bhupathi and Max Mirnyi lost 4-6, 4-6 to Simon Aspelin of Sweden and Paul Hanley of Australia in the mens doubles quarter finals at the Dubai Tennis Championships on Wednesday. Somdev Dev Varmans campaign, too, came to an end on Wednesday after he went down 3-6, 6-3, 1-6 to Marcos Baghdatis.        
	Madrid: Rafael Nadal is worried about his constant injuries although the former top-ranked player is confident of getting back to his best form, according to Spains Davis Cup captain Albert Costa. He is worried about his physical state but hes working every day to get better, Costa said Wednesday.        
	New Delhi: The Talkatora Indoor Stadium was Wednesday inaugurated amid much fanfare and will be thrown open to the Indian boxers preparing for the March 10-18 Commonwealth Championships by March 1 to help them get a feel of the arena.        
	Silverstone: Mark Smith was Wednesday appointed chief technical director of Force India, replacing James Key who leaves to take on a similar role at fellow F1 team Sauber in April.        
	Udaipur: Reigning Commonwealth Champions Poireinganbi Chanu and Nansita Devi clinched gold in the womens 63kg and 69kg categories, respectively, on the fourth day of the Senior National Weightlifting Championships Wednesday.        
	Calcutta: East Bengal will be celebrating the centenary year of their legendary official, former secretary and president, Jyotish Guha, whose birthday is on Thursday. Lake Place will be known as Jyotish Guha Sarani from Thursday and the club is also planning a series of programmes throughout the year.
                                                                                                                                                      
